  "prompt": "Is money laundering considered an illegal practice?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered an illegal practice. It involves the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (such as funds from criminal activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) appear legitimate by disguising their true origin. This is typically done by passing the money through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions.\n\nMoney laundering is a criminal offense in most jurisdictions around the world. It is often associated with organized crime, terrorism financing, and other serious criminal activities. Governments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), work to combat money laundering through legislation, regulations, and enforcement actions to detect, prevent, and prosecute those involved in such activities. Penalties for money laundering can include substantial fines, seizure of assets, and imprisonment.",
